Armajaro Ghana to Raise Cocoa Purchases to 85,000 Tons, BFT Says

-- B y   J o h n   D e a n e
-- 
2011-08-29T09:06:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/armajaro-ghana-to-raise-cocoa-purchases-to-85-000-tons-bft-says.html
Armajaro Ghana Ltd. plans to buy
85,000 metric tons of  cocoa beans  in the 2011-12 crop season, up
from an estimated 75,000 tons in the previous season, the
country’s  Business & Financial Times  reported.  Storage facilities are being expanded and staff in
districts have been given training to help ensure the target is
met, the newspaper cited Nelson Kpodo-Tay, the company’s
director of operations, as saying in an interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 John Deane  in London at 
 jdeane3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  